## ðŸ—‚ Step 1: Set Up Your Google Drive Structure

Create a new folder called:  
`My Business App`

Inside it, add:

- `/Forms` â€“ (optional) store Google Forms
- `/Sheets` â€“ store your working databases
- `/Photos` â€“ store photo uploads
- `/PDFs` â€“ optional download folder
- `/Client Files` â€“ optional client-specific folders

---

## ðŸ“Š Step 2: Create a Google Sheet

Create a Google Sheet named: `Work_Reports`

Add column headers like:

| Timestamp | Client | Date | Worker | Task | Location | Notes | Image |
|-----------|--------|------|--------|------|----------|-------|--------|

*Optional:* Add a second sheet for `Maintenance Logs`, `Consultations`, or `Scheduling`.

---

## ðŸ“ Step 3: (Optional) Create a Google Form

You can skip this and let AppSheet handle form submissions.  
But if you want to:

- Go to [Google Forms](https://forms.google.com)
- Create a new form
- Link it to your Sheet (Responses tab â†’ Link to Sheets)
- Match your columns from above

---

## ðŸ“± Step 4: Create Your App in AppSheet

1. Go to: [https://www.appsheet.com](https://www.appsheet.com)
2. Click `Start for free`
3. Choose your Google Sheet from Step 2
4. AppSheet will auto-generate a working app from your data

---

## ðŸŽ¨ Step 5: Customize the App

### ðŸ–¼ï¸ Change View Types

Use these views:
- **Deck View** â€“ for card-style lists
- **Table View** â€“ spreadsheet-style
- **Form View** â€“ submit new reports
- **Detail View** â€“ show one record in full
- **Dashboard View** â€“ combine multiple views

> Go to **UX > Views** to edit or create views

---

### ðŸ§­ Setup Navigation

- Rename views to: `Work Reports`, `Maintenance`, `Consultations`
- Rearrange tabs by dragging in **UX > Navigation**
- Optionally switch to **Bottom Navigation Bar** in **UX > Options**

---

### ðŸ§© Add Form Inputs

Go to **Data > Columns**, then:
- Set `Image` column type to `Image`
- Set `Location` to `LatLong` (optional for GPS)
- Set dropdowns (Enum) if you want fixed choices

---

## ðŸ”’ Step 6: Share the App

1. Go to **Users > Users**
2. Add email addresses of your team
3. Set the app to **Private**

If your team is all using Google accounts, they can log in securely.

---

## ðŸ“Ž Optional Features to Try

- **Security Filters** â€“ show each worker only their reports
- **Slices** â€“ filtered views by type, date, or location
- **Quick Edits** â€“ let users update task status quickly
- **Image Capture** â€“ from mobile device camera
- **PDF Export** â€“ use AppSheetâ€™s built-in print/download view

